Post Description



We are currently looking for a bioinformatician familiar

with the computing infrastructure used for Illumina HiSeq sequencing and

sequencing data quality control. The Genomics Unit

(http://www.crg.es/genomics_unit) provides service to clients from within t
he

CRG/PRBB, as well as to external users. The Unit has established workflows 
for

many different types of high-throughput sequencing projects, including geno
mic sequencing,

mRNA-Seq, and ChIP-Seq, and is equipped with two Illumina HiSeq sequencing

instruments. Additional instrument purchases are foreseen as new technologi
es

become available.





Main responsibilities



Specific tasks of the position in the context of

sequencing data production bioinformatics will include:

Quality control of sequencing runs using established

pipelines; development and implementation of new workflows for data quality

control and data interpretation; LIMS (laboratory information managment

system)-based run management; Illumina software upgrades and maintenance of

data archive; making sequencing data and run reports available to users of 
the

Unit.

Aside from that, the candidate will analyse data from technology

implementation projects and experimental sequencing runs.





Candidate requirements



Experience:

Experience in handling and analysing Illumina data and

Proficiency with a scripting language such as Perl experienced in using R f
or

data analysis.

Experience with managing databases and LIMS systems is

essential.

Knowledge in molecular biology and/or molecular genetics

is desirable. The post requires a client-oriented attitude, as well as an

interest for scientific questions that can be addressed using novel high-th
roughput

sequencing technologies.



Degree:

Master's degree or Ph.D. in computer sciences,

bioinformatics, biostatistics or related discipline.



Language:

Fluent in English.



